  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">REACH - Cash for Work IRQ161</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This Cash for Work (CfW) intervention would serve the IDPs, returnees and remainees in Mosul in order address food and shelter insecurities and support struggling governmental service projects. In response to expressed needs by leading officials in the Ministry of Trade and Directorate of Seed distribution and Mosul Harvest Warehouse Silo in the Bzwaya area, a district of Central Mosul, Ninevah governorate, 15 km of east outside of Mosul. the activities under this CfW project will potentially include providing needed support for the silo.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This CfW initiative will be addressing and providing support in the areas of livelihood/social cohesion and providing work that would otherwise not be done due to the present limited capacity of government, as well as offer relief to affected populations of IDPs, returnees and remainees. Indirectly, this CfW will provide support for the farmers need seed for next harvesting season and the public whom the government supply wheat powder and who depend on the silo. making their work easier and the services provided by the silo more dependable. The government will also benefit as this CfW is providing a service that at this time they are not able to do, therefore this action will improve the overall reputation and level of trust people have in the government and the silo which is essential during this fragile time. Lastly, the family members of cfw workers will economically benefit from project.</narrative>
  </description>
